@500 = ~M'Khiin continued her endless wandering long after parting ways with <CHARNAME>. From dungeons to forests to the clamor of cities, she drifted, never lingering long enough for roots to take hold. In time, her road carried her to Sigil, where even a goblin could vanish among the throng of outcasts and planar wanderers.

There, among kin from distant worlds, she glimpsed fragments of what goblins might yet become: not mere scavengers but keepers of an older, subtler knowledge long forgotten on the Material Plane.

Yet the weight of old wounds and disappointments proved too heavy. M'Khiin slipped away once more. She drifted like a half-remembered dream, never staying long enough to nurture something greater.

“My story,” she would say when pressed, "is my own. And when I join the spirits, it will pass with me."~

@501 = ~M'Khiin wandered for a time after her adventures with <CHARNAME>. Within her she carried incredible knowledge: that goblins need not be defined by bloodshed, nor forever bound to the cruelties of their past.

In Sigil she sought out her scattered kin and drank deep of the lore they preserved. Armed with these reclaimed fragments, she felt the pull of home grow stronger. Not the tribe who had once caged her, but a fragile refuge she found the courage to build.

With patience and quiet resolve, M'Khiin gathered others like her, outcast goblins weary of raids and violence. She taught them to value community, building a small tribe where trust replaced treachery. 

In those hidden corners of her refuge, a new generation of goblins listened. They learned. And, in time, they began to believe in a brighter future.~